payload.text:
I have implemented fixes to better support portrait images across the application.

1.  **Restaurant Modal**: I've updated the image viewer to use a "blurred background" technique. The main image is now displayed using `object-contain` so the full photo is always visible, while a blurred, zoomed-in version of the same photo fills the background to eliminate black bars.
2.  **City Pages**: I changed the restaurant card aspect ratio from landscape (`4:3`) to portrait (`3:4`). This allows portrait photos to be displayed much larger in the list without cropping heads or feet.
3.  **Gallery Preview**: I updated the scrolling gallery at the bottom of the home page to use portrait-oriented cards instead of landscape ones.

# Updated files:

## components/RestaurantModal.tsx

Updated the image section to layer the full image over a blurred background version of itself.

